HEADWORD: Boulangerite
<hw>Bou*lan"ger*ite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<etsep>Boulanger</etsep>, a French mineralogist.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of a bluish gray color and metallic
luster, usually in plumose masses, also compact. It is a sulphide of
antimony and lead.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boulangism</ent>⟦br⟧
